# 14 : BACKEND — bespoke x86-64 + per-platform dispatch
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ THESIS
  stage0 : Cranelift-CPU + rspirv-GPU (expedient, Rust-hosted)
  stage1+ : owned x86-64 backend + owned SPIR-V emitter + all-platforms
  ≡ R4 (bespoke) + R5 (cross-platform) + R18 (host-submit matrix)

§ OWNED x86-64 BACKEND (stage1+)
  input : MIR cssl-dialect (§§ 02+15)
  phases :
    1 : isel — instruction-selection tables (tree-matching + peephole)
    2 : regalloc — graph-color + linear-scan hybrid (per-fn choice by-heuristic)
    3 : schedule — list-scheduler with latency-model per-µarch
    4 : emit — machine-code bytes + reloc + debug-info
  µarchs supported :
    intel-alder-lake-cove (12gen P-core)
    intel-raptor-lake (13/14gen P-core)
    intel-meteor-lake (Core-Ultra-1 P-core)
    intel-arrow-lake (Core-Ultra-2)
    AMD-zen4 + zen5 (via feature-detect)
    generic-x86-64-v3 baseline
  SIMD :
    AVX2 base (guaranteed-v3)
    AVX-512 opportunistic (runtime-CPU-dispatch)
    multi-variant fat-kernels for hot paths
  ABI :
    SysV-AMD64 (Linux + Mac-Intel)
    Windows-x64 (MSVC-compat)
    Darwin (Mac-Intel + Rosetta-2 for ARM-Mac)
  debug-info :
    DWARF-5 emit (Linux + Mac)
    CodeView + PDB (Windows, stage-1.5)
  size-target : ≤ 15K LOC CSSLv3 self-hosted

§ OWNED SPIR-V EMITTER (stage1+)
  input : MIR cssl-dialect + spirv-dialect
  replaces rspirv with hand-rolled typed-builder (3-5K LOC)
  spec-conformance : validator-identical to spirv-val
  structured-CFG direct-emission (CC4)
  capability-tracking automatic from used-ops
  deduplication : types, constants, decorations

§ OWNED DXIL EMITTER (stage2)
  input : MIR cssl-dialect
  replaces DirectXShaderCompiler-offline-shim
  D3D12 shader-model 6.6+ (mesh + RT + cooperative-matrix)
  root-signature auto-generated from effect-row + layout-attrs
  DXBC-compatibility : v1 skips (SM 6.6+ only)

§ OWNED MSL EMITTER (stage2)
  input : MIR cssl-dialect
  replaces spirv-cross --msl
  Metal-3 baseline (mesh + RT + cooperative-matrix on Apple-Silicon)
  argument-buffers for bindless
  fn-constant for specialization

§ OWNED WGSL EMITTER (stage2)
  input : MIR cssl-dialect
  replaces Tint
  WebGPU spec-current (naga-compatible)
  no-BDA (emits struct-of-arrays binding pattern)
  ray-query optional (when available)

§ HOST-SUBMIT BACKENDS
  Vulkan-1.4   : stage0 ash crate | stage1+ owned FFI (volk-like dispatch)
  Level-Zero   : stage0 level-zero-sys | stage1+ owned FFI
                 (R18 telemetry primary backing on Intel)
  D3D12        : stage0 windows-rs | stage1+ owned FFI
  Metal        : stage0 metal crate | stage1+ owned Objective-C-bridge
  WebGPU       : stage0 wgpu-core | stage1+ direct browser-API (JS-interop)
  GNM (PS5)    : platform-SDK, NDA-gated, stub in public-CI
  NVN (Sw2)    : platform-SDK, NDA-gated, stub in public-CI
  per-backend adapter-layer shared-interface :
    create_device, create_queue, create_cmd_buffer,
    bind_resources, dispatch/draw, submit, wait,
    telemetry_capture, sysman_query

§ AUDIO HOST BACKENDS (S7-F3 / T11-D81 — render-only stage-0)
  scope : output (render) only at stage-0 ; capture (microphone) DEFERRED
          per PRIME-DIRECTIVE consent + UI-affordance gate
  WASAPI       : stage0 windows-rs | stage1+ owned FFI
                 IAudioClient + IAudioRenderClient
                 shared-mode (mix-format negotiation) + exclusive-mode
                 thread-affinity contract : caller must CoInitializeEx
  ALSA         : stage0 hand-rolled FFI via libloading
                 (libasound.so.2 + libpulse.so.0 dynamic-load)
                 PulseAudio preferred when libpulse.so.0 present
                 fallback ALSA direct when PA absent
                 gate-skip when neither installed
  CoreAudio    : stage0 hand-rolled FFI via libloading
                 (AudioToolbox.framework + CoreAudio.framework)
                 AudioComponentInstance + AudioUnit (default-output)
                 macOS only (cfg-gated)
  per-backend adapter-layer shared-interface :
    open_default_output, query_format,
    submit_frames (push-mode), poll_padding,
    close, last_error
  sample-format canonical : f32 interleaved channels
    platform layer converts to/from device-native-format at boundary
  ring-buffer : deterministic latency budget
    default 256-frame @ 48kHz = 5.3ms
    configurable via AudioStreamConfig.frame_buffer_size
  underrun policy :
    poll padding via platform-specific API (WASAPI : GetCurrentPadding ;
      ALSA : snd_pcm_avail_update ; CoreAudio : output-callback timing)
    emit AudioEvent::Underrun (telemetry-ring placeholder) — never silent-drop
  sample-rate negotiation :
    request → device-format query → if mismatch + can't negotiate :
      fail-loud (AudioError::SampleRateMismatch)
    linear-resample at boundary DEFERRED to stdlib DSP slice
  capture-mode (DEFERRED — PRIME-DIRECTIVE) :
    rationale — microphone-input is surveillance-adjacent
    explicit consent + UI-affordance not yet designed
    capture path WILL be implemented behind {Sensitive<"microphone">}
      effect + audit-policy gate when UI-affordance lands
    audio-loopback to system-output-recording is FORBIDDEN per PRIME-DIRECTIVE
  DSP primitives : NONE at stage-0 (deferred to stdlib slice post-F)
§ HOST-NET (S7-F4 / T11-D82 — networking host backend)
  thesis : per-platform networking surface for TCP + UDP bound to
           connection-oriented + datagram primitives. Sits below
           `stdlib/net.cssl` (the source-level surface) and exposes
           the FFI symbols (`__cssl_net_*`) consumed by emitted code.
  Win32        : Winsock 2.2 ; hand-rolled `extern "system"` bindings
                 to ws2_32.dll (no `windows-sys` crate dep at S7-F4 ;
                 matches B5 file-IO discipline). WSAStartup/WSACleanup
                 ref-counted internally so partial-init is handled.
  Linux+macOS  : BSD-sockets ; hand-rolled `extern "C"` bindings to
                 libc (no `libc` crate dep). Apocky's host is Windows ;
                 the Unix path is structurally tested (compile-only)
                 until a non-Windows CI runner exists, mirroring B5.
  Stage1+      : owned FFI dispatch (volk-like vtable for Win32 ;
                 syscall-direct on Linux), TLS via owned implementation
                 (or BoringSSL bridge), getaddrinfo wiring for
                 hostname resolution, IPv6 (`SocketAddrV6`).
  Crate layout :
    cssl-rt::net          ← portable surface : flags / NetError / counters
                              / last-error / cap-system
    cssl-rt::net_win32    ← Winsock2 platform layer (cfg-gated)
    cssl-rt::net_unix     ← BSD-sockets platform layer (cfg-gated)
    cssl-rt::ffi          ← __cssl_net_* FFI shims (15 symbols)
    cssl-host-net         ← high-level Rust API
                              (TcpListener / TcpStream / UdpSocket /
                              SocketAddrV4 / NetError / caps facade)
    stdlib/net.cssl       ← source-level CSSLv3 surface
    cssl-mir::body_lower  ← syntactic recognizer for `net::*` bare-name
                              calls → cssl.net.* MIR ops
  PRIME-DIRECTIVE attestation : every connect-style / bind-style call
    routes through `cssl_rt::net::check_caps_for_addr` BEFORE the
    syscall fires. Default cap-set = LOOPBACK only ; non-loopback
    requires explicit `caps_grant(NET_CAP_OUTBOUND | NET_CAP_INBOUND)`.
    Raw / packet sockets DEFERRED ; TLS DEFERRED ; IPv6 DEFERRED.
    See `specs/11_IFC.csl § PRIME-DIRECTIVE ENCODING § NET-CAP rules`
    for the full cap algebra.

§ BACKEND-MATRIX (ref §§ 00 + §§ 10)
  backend     graphics  compute   RT      XMX        power      scope
  Vulkan-1.4  ✓         ✓         ✓       via-coop   advisory   portable
  Level-Zero  ✗         ✓✓        ✗       direct     direct     Intel
  D3D12       ✓         ✓         ✓       via-coop   advisory   Windows
  Metal       ✓         ✓         ✓       coop       advisory   Apple
  WebGPU      ✓         ✓         ◐       ◐          ✗          browser
  GNM         ✓         ✓         ✓       ◐          platform   console
  NVN         ✓         ✓         ◐       ◐          platform   console

§ EFFECT-DIRECTED BACKEND-SELECTION
  {Backend<B>} effect in fn-sig forces B for-this-fn
  {Target<P>} effect gates platform-specific code-paths
  compiler-choice logic :
    ∀ fn with {GPU} and no explicit Backend :
      choose most-capable available on-target-platform
    priority on Intel : Level-Zero > Vulkan (for pure-compute)
                        Vulkan > Level-Zero (for graphics/RT)
    on NVIDIA / AMD : Vulkan only (v1)
    on Apple : Metal primary
    on Windows : Vulkan primary, D3D12 opt-in
    on Browser : WebGPU only
  overrides explicit via {Backend<...>}

§ FAT-BINARY ASSEMBLY
  linker merges :
    host-obj variants per-OS-target (ELF | COFF | Mach-O)
    gpu-blobs per-API (SPIR-V | DXIL | MSL | WGSL)
    telemetry-schema metadata
    audit-manifest signed
  single .cssl-bin contains all-needed blobs
  runtime-loader selects per-platform at-launch

§ RUNTIME LOADER (libcssl-rt)
  startup-sequence :
    1 : detect-OS + detect-CPU-features
    2 : enumerate-GPU-devices via chosen-backend
    3 : load-matching gpu-blobs from-fat-binary
    4 : init-telemetry-ring (R18)
    5 : verify-audit-manifest-signature (R16 + §§ 11)
    6 : hand-over to-application-entry
  dispatch-tables populated per-detected-hardware
  L0 + Vulkan may-coexist on Intel (compute-pipeline on L0,
    graphics-pipeline on Vulkan, shared SPIR-V modules)

§ CROSS-BACKEND SPIR-V REUSE
  one SPIR-V blob consumed-by : Vulkan, Level-Zero, WebGPU(via-translation)
  ≡ test Vulkan-L0 differential-equivalence (§§ 23)
  DXIL + MSL + WGSL : per-platform translations OR owned-emitters
  compiler optimization : emit-shared-SPIR-V once, translate-on-demand

§ CONSOLE STUBS
  public-repo : stubbed-symbols + documentation-only
  private-repo : platform-SDK integration + NDA-compliant code
  CI-public : skip console-runs, emit "platform-sdk-not-available"
  CI-internal : full platform testing behind access-gate

§ SIZE + TIME BUDGETS
  stage0 binary : ≤ 50 MB (cranelift + rspirv + deps)
  stage1 binary : ≤ 20 MB (self-contained)
  compile-time stage0 : 2s incremental, 30s clean (medium-project)
  compile-time stage1 : 1s incremental, 15s clean (same project, own-backend)
  runtime startup : ≤ 100ms initialization overhead

§ TESTING BACKEND-INDEPENDENCE (§§ 23)
  differential-tests : same source → multiple backends → compare outputs
  golden-pixel-regression per-backend per-example
  backend-feature-parity matrix CI-enforced
  sysman-capture per-backend where-available

§ ASSET-PIPELINE  (N1 / T11-D104 — game-asset parsers + loaders)
  thesis : layer between cssl-rt's fs-IO surface (T11-D76) + runtime data
           structures . CSSLv3-app . parsers Rust-hosted-stage0 ;
           surface mirrors eventual self-hosted-CSSLv3 form
           ⇒ consumers migrate-mechanically.
  surface = always-on (formats stage-0)
    PNG  : decode + encode + peek
           8-bit (gray / gray+alpha / RGB / RGBA)
           hand-rolled zlib/DEFLATE inflate (BTYPE=0 stored + BTYPE=1
             fixed-Huffman ; BTYPE=2 dynamic-Huffman → UnsupportedKind +
             follow-up slice)
           CRC + Adler-32 verified
           round-trip byte-stable (re-encode equality)
    GLTF : decode_glb (binary container) + decode_gltf (text JSON)
           hand-rolled minimal JSON parser (objects + arrays + strings +
             numbers + booleans + null + Unicode-BMP escapes)
             cap : MAX_JSON_DEPTH = 64
           full glTF-2.0 schema subset :
             asset + scenes + nodes (TRS + matrix) + meshes + accessors +
             bufferViews + buffers + animations + skins + materials
             (PBR-Metallic-Roughness) + images + textures
           scene-graph walker (depth-first) + accessor → byte-slice
             resolution against embedded GLB BIN chunk
    WAV  : decode + encode
           RIFF/WAVE PCM (PcmU8 / PcmS16 / PcmS24 / PcmS32) +
             IEEE 754 float32 (format-tag 3)
           round-trip byte-stable
           unknown chunks (LIST etc.) skipped silently per RIFF
    TTF  : parse + glyph_index + glyph_outline + glyph_metric
           header + table-directory + 8 required tables :
             head + maxp + hhea + hmtx + loca + glyf + cmap-format-4 + name
           simple-glyph outlines : delta-encoded Sub/Up/Average/Paeth
             filter pipeline
  surface = always-on (infrastructure stage-0)
    AssetHandle<T>   : async-loading scaffold
                       state ∈ {Pending, Ready(T), Failed(AssetError),
                                Cancelled}
                       stage-0 every handle = Ready (synchronous)
                       Pending reachable only when async-runtime lands
                       LoadProgress reports bytes_done / bytes_total
    AssetBudget      : per-class memory cap + eviction
                       AssetClass ∈ {Texture, Model, Audio, Font, Blob,
                                     Other(name)}
                       EvictionPolicy ∈ {Lru, SmallestFirst}
                       try_reserve refuses above-cap requests
                       reserve_with_eviction evicts older entries
    AssetWatcher     : hot-reload surface
                       watch_path(path) → AssetWatcher
                       WatchEvent ∈ {Created, Modified, Deleted, Renamed,
                                     Overflow}
                       stage-0 inert (in-memory queue ; push_event drives)
                       OS-backed (Win32 ReadDirectoryChangesW / Linux
                         inotify / macOS FSEvents) follow-up slice
    AssetError       : single sum-type unifying all parser failures
                       Io / Truncated / BadMagic / UnsupportedKind /
                       BadChecksum / InvalidValue / BudgetExceeded /
                       Watcher / Encode
                       each constructor carries enough context for clear
                         surface messages (path + reason / format + site /
                         expected-vs-actual integers)
  invariants (PRIME-DIRECTIVE preservation)
    every parser caps allocation at input-reported-size + hard upper bound
      png::MAX_IMAGE_BYTES     = 256 MB
      wav::MAX_WAV_DATA_BYTES  = 256 MB
      gltf::MAX_JSON_DEPTH     = 64
    pathological inputs rejected BEFORE allocation
      zero-dim images / integer-overflow buffer sizes / deeply-nested JSON
    no URI auto-fetch — text-mode glTF returns uri strings ;
      consumer resolves
    no directory traversal — watch_path opens exactly the named path
    no telemetry — counters local ; no global-ring at stage-0
    no microphone / camera / system-font enumeration / clipboard /
      env-var read / screenshot
    file-IO parser ¬ input-device
  deferred (follow-up slices)
    texture : WebP / KTX2 read (cfg-gated)
    audio   : OGG-Vorbis / MP3 decode (compressed streams cfg-gated)
    font    : bitmap (BDF / PCF / sfnt-bitmap) + CFF / CFF2 outlines
              (OTTO scaler) + composite glyphs in glyf + GPOS / GSUB
              (kerning + ligatures + complex scripts) + variable
              fonts (fvar / gvar) + color fonts (COLR / CPAL)
    PNG     : 16-bit-per-channel + paletted (PLTE) + Adam7 interlacing
              + DEFLATE BTYPE=2 dynamic-Huffman inflate
    GLTF    : KHR_* extension typed consumption + URI data: scheme decode
              + JSON-Schema validation
    async   : real future-based loading
    watcher : real OS-backed event delivery + debouncer + dispatcher
    DXT     : GPU-side BC1/BC3/BC7 compressor (separate slice)
  spec-corpus
    this section authored at T11-D104 ; future N-axis slices append
    sub-sections (texture-compression, audio-decode, font-layout) as
    they land.

∎ BACKEND
